# Conclusion

The application was vulnerable to a CL.TE HTTP Request Smuggling attack caused by inconsistent request parsing between the front-end and back-end servers. By exploiting this desynchronization, it was possible to bypass front-end access controls, access the internal administrative interface, and execute privileged functionality, resulting in the successful deletion of the target user.
